{
  "stem": "2581.8",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh yes, one time my father went to take out the rations which we have received and Rumkowski, the leader of the ghetto, surrounded that place and checked the IDs of the people that were getting their rations.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he found out that my father should have been at work and not getting the rations, and he put him in the prison where from this prison no one came back alive.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "No one came back.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was called [NON-ENGLISH], and if you were sent to [NON-ENGLISH] that means you were sent outside the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Well, here I was this young boy, very little experience in life except these things that were happening during the war years.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I ran to the-- in every factory you had the police commissar, and I ran into him.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He knew my father, and he knew-- first I went to the technical leader, [GERMAN], and he took me to the commissioner and talked about my father.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He was a good worker, et cetera, et cetera.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "He got him out.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Or he came back, you know.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "At that time, I remember, whatever potatoes I had in the house, I had boiled them and brought them to the prison for my father.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I figured, that's his last night, at least don't let him go hungry.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "When he came back we had nothing to eat, but it was worth it.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We helped each other.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "If not for my father, I wouldn't be sitting here today.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "My father saved my life.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Later on, he saved my life.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So when the order came to leave the ghetto, which was in August '44, we tried to hide.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were so lucky to pick a hiding place where underneath was a bakery, and that smell of the bread was killing us.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
